Go ahead and use electrical heat! Get out a suitably rated orange =
extension cord and 24 hour timer and the space heater. Set it to start =
soon enough to heat the beast before you go out. Unplug and go. I'm no EE, =
but you won't use more than 10-20 cents worth of reddy kilowatt. Should =
save you time in the morning too. Along the same lines I'd bet that the =
energy cost of a incandesent drop light to warm the motor would cost less =
than the gas and engine wear used to do the same thing.=20

-Harry in sunny Fresno


